HEADWORD: Pucelle
<hw>Pu*celle"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. LL.
<ets>pulicella</ets>, fr. L. <ets>pullus</ets> a young animal. See
<er>Pullet</er>.]</ety> <def>A maid; a virgin.</def> <altsp>[Written
also <asp>pucel</asp>.]</altsp> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Lady or <qex>pucelle</qex>, that wears mask or fan.</q>
<rj><qau>B. Jonson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>La Pucelle</b></col>, <cd>the Maid of Orleans, Joan of
Arc.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Puceron</ent>⟦br⟧
